		<body>
			<div type="leaf">
				<p>
					<pb facs="#f011"/>
					<metamark facs="#f011_z000" function="folio" n="12" place="top right" rend="pencil">12</metamark>
				</p>
				<p>But unlike Shakespeare, who was forced <lb/>to <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z001" hand="#HM" rend="multi-stroke">it</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z002" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z003" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">the contrary course</add> by circumstances, Hawthorne <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z004" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">,</del><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z004" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">(</add>either from <lb/>simple disinclination, or else from inaptitude) <lb/>refrains from all the <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z005" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">roar[?]</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z006" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z007" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">popularizing noise</add> and show of <lb/>broad farce, <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z008" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">or</del><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z008" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">&amp;</add> blood-besmeared tragedy; <lb/>content with the still, rich utterance<add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z009" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">s</add> of a <lb/>great intellect in repose, and which sends <lb/>few thoughts into circulation, except they be <lb/>arterialized <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z010" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">in</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z011" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="no-caret">at</add> his large warm lungs, and <lb/>expanded in his honest heart. <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z012" function="new-para" place="inline" rend="bracket">[</metamark>Nor need you <lb/>fix upon that blackness in him, if it suit <lb/>you not. Nor, indeed, will all readers discern <lb/>it, for it is, <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z013" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">only</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z014" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="no-caret">mostly,</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z015" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">intrusted</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z017" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z016" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">insinuated</add> to those who may <lb/>best undersand it, and account for it; it is <lb/>not obtruded upon every one alike.</p>
				<p>     Some may start to read of Shakespeare and <lb/>Hawthorne on the same page. They may say, that if <lb/>an illustration were needed, a lesser light might have <lb/>sufficed to elucidate this Hawthorne, this <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z018" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z019" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">small</add> man of <lb/>yesterday. But I am not, willingly, one of those, who, <lb/>as touching Shakespeare at least, exemplify the <lb/>maxim of Rochefoucault, that "we exalt the reputation <lb/>of some, in order to depress that of others"<add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z020" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="no-caret">;--</add> who, to <lb/>teach all <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z021" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">tyros</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z022" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z024" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret"><del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z023" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">me</del> noble-souled aspirants</add> that there is no hope for them, <lb/>pronounce Shakespeare absolutely unapproachable. <lb/><del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z025" hand="#HM" rend="overwritten">but</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z025" hand="#HM" place="inline" rend="overwritten">But</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z026" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">he</del> <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z028" function="caret" place="inline" rend="guideline">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z027" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">Shakespeare</add> has been approached. There are minds <lb/>that have gone as <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z029" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z030" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">far</add> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z031" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">deep</del> as Shakespeare into <lb/>the universe. And hardly a mortal man, <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z032" hand="#HM" rend="single-stroke">that</del> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z033" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="no-caret">who,</add> <lb/>at some time or other, has not felt <del change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z034" hand="#HM" rend="multi-stroke">at some</del><lb/>as great thoughts in him as any you will find <lb/>in Hamlet. We must not <metamark change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z035" function="caret" place="inline" rend="caret">^</metamark><add change="#StBa" facs="#f011_z036" hand="#HM" place="above" rend="caret">inferentially</add> malign mankind</p>
			</div>
